<li id="cite_note-waxmanpage-69"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-waxmanpage_69-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20061207032614/http://democrats.reform.house.gov/features/politics_and_science/index.htm">"Politics and Science: Investigating the Bush Administration's Promotion of Ideology Over Science"</a>. August 2003. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.house.gov/reform/min/politicsandscience/">the original</a> on 7 December 2006.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Politics+and+Science%3A+Investigating+the+Bush+Administration%27s+Promotion+of+Ideology+Over+Science&amp;rft.date=2003-08&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.house.gov%2Freform%2Fmin%2Fpoliticsandscience%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APoliticization+of+science" class="Z3988"></span></span>
